<div id="highlights">
  <div class="inner">
    <div class="point">
      <h2>No CLI/API required</h2>
      <p>
        Runs as a single container, no database required. Policies and trigger types are specified in your application deployment files or Helm charts. 
        Keel extends Kubernetes without adding complexity.
      </p>
    </div>  

    <div class="point">
      <h2>Policy-driven updates</h2>
      <p>        
        In order for Keel Just specify on the applications themselves, when you want them to be updated, i.e. from 0.1.0 to 0.2.0 (minor) 
        or only major versions.
      </p>
    </div> 

    <div class="point">
      <h2>Open Source</h2>
      <p>
          Keel is Open Source and was designed to be easily extendable. Providers, triggers and notification mechanisms are just default interface implementations. 
          If you need Nomad, Docker Swarm or Mesos support, it's easy to add it.
      </p>
    </div>      
